CISC251 - Data Analytics Data Visualization

# Load packages
library(tidyverse)
# Read the touched up csv file for mostfreq1000docword
fw <- read.csv("mostFreq1000wordData.csv", check.names = FALSE)

# Want: Sum of all the columns, sum those sums and create a stack bar graph, fill by word. x-axis is POS, y-axis is sums

# Compute column sums of the 1000 words (Gets total frequency for all speeches)
sums <- data.frame(Sums = colSums(fw[4:1003]))

# Convert rownames to column
sums <- rownames_to_column(sums, "Word_POS")

# Separate Word and POS tag
sums <- separate(sums, col = 1, into = c("Word", "POS"), sep = '_')

# POS Tags in mostfreq1000wordData.csv
PoS = c("ABN", "ABX", "AP", "AT", "BE", "BED", "BEDZ", "BEG", "BEM", "BEN", "BER", "BEZ", "CC", "CD", "CS", "DO", "DOD", "DOZ", "DT", "DTI", "DTS", "EX", "HV", "HVD", "HVG", "HVZ", "IN", "JJ", "JJR", "JJS", "JJT", "MD", "NIL", "NN", "NN$", "NNS", "NP", "NP$", "NPS", "NR", "OD", "PN", "PP$", "PPLS", "PPO", "PPS", "PPSS", "QL", "QLP", "RB", "RBR", "RN", "RP", "TO", "UH", "VB", "VBD", "VBG", "VBN", "VBZ", "WDT.", "WP$", "WPS", "WQL", "WRB")

# Empty list to store bar graphs
bg = list()

# Normalize function to range [0, 1]
min_max_norm <- function(x) {
    (x - min(x)) / (max(x) - min(x))
}

# Create a normalized dataframe of sums
sums_norm <- as.data.frame(lapply(sums[3], min_max_norm))

# Join dataframes
sums <- cbind(sums, sums_norm)

# Rename columns
colnames(sums) <- c("Word", "POS", "Sums", "Normalized Sums")

# Display sums
sums

# Create bar graphs for each POS tag. x-axis = word, y-axis = sum
for (p in 1:length(PoS)) {
  bg[[p]] <- sums %>%
    filter(POS == PoS[p]) %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = Word, y = `Normalized Sums`, label = Sums)) +
      geom_col(position = "stack") +
      ylim(0, 1) +
      scale_x_discrete(guide = guide_axis(n.dodge=25)) +
      ggtitle(PoS[p]) +
      theme_classic()
  print(bg[[p]])
}


# Find interesting words (most frequent)
sums %>%
  filter(`Normalized Sums` > mean(`Normalized Sums`)) %>%
  arrange(desc(Sums))

# Create data frame that sums frequency for each POS tag
posSums <- sums %>%
          group_by(POS) %>%
          summarise(`Total Sum` = sum(Sums), .groups = 'drop')

# Convert table to data frame
posSums <- as.data.frame(posSums)

# Display posSums
posSums

# Make a bar graph from least to greatest value of Sums for POS tags
posSums %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(POS, `Total Sum`), y = `Total Sum`)) +
    geom_col(width = .5, fill = "#00b2ee") +
    scale_x_discrete(guide = guide_axis(n.dodge=5)) +
    labs(title = "Total Frequency of POS Tags in Ascending Order",
         x = "POS",
         y = "Total Frequency") +
    theme_classic() +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = rel(3)),
          plot.title.position = "plot", 
          axis.title.y = element_text(size = rel(2)), 
          axis.title.x = element_text(size = rel(2)),
          axis.text.x = element_text(size = rel(1.75)),
          axis.text.y = element_text(size = rel(1.75)),
          legend.position = "none"
    )
